</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Dav.</SPEAKER>
<STAGE><HI>[To the</HI> Servant]</STAGE>
<P>Go to your Lady: tell her all is well. You'll find her brother with her Captain Dormer; take him a&s;ide, and tell him to repair to me without a moment's lo&s;s: your diligence &s;hall be rewarded. Go: make ha&s;te.</P>
<STAGE><HI>[Exit</HI> Servant.</STAGE>
<P>Now the di&s;covery's out&mdash;I told you Ma|rianne had &s;een her hu&s;band; his chariot pa&s;&s;ing her window was &s;topt by accident in the &s;treet; the mob and clamour u&s;ual on &s;uch occa&s;ions at|tracted her notice and that of the neighbours: my &s;ervant now informs me 'twas the equipage of Sir Harry Harlow.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Lady D.</SPEAKER>
<P>What do you &s;ay? Sir Harry Har|low's!&mdash;no; it mu&s;t not be. Revoke that word.</P>
