<P>I flew with ardour at your &s;um|mons; and I await your plea&s;ure, with a heart that throbs to &s;erve you&mdash;with a heart, dear Lady, that can only cea&s;e to love, when it &s;hall cea&s;e to beat.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Lady D.</SPEAKER>
