<P>Mo&s;t amiable of women!&mdash;I per|ceive your drift: you act too nobly by an un|de&s;erving hu&s;band; but I make no appeal; implicitly I &s;hall obey, becau&s;e 'tis your com|mand;&mdash;and tho' my life were made the &s;acri|fice, what were more glorious than to die for you?&mdash;one word, one kind approving look can overpay the purcha&s;e; grant that before we part, and at your feet I dedicate for ever to your &s;ervice my devoted heart.</P>
